1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 25=

4
00:01:38,287 --> 00:01:40,336
Jiaqiao, tell me the truth.

5
00:01:40,966 --> 00:01:42,605
Did he tell you the reason

6
00:01:42,606 --> 00:01:43,897
I broke up with him?

7
00:01:44,446 --> 00:01:45,725
Was it because

8
00:01:45,726 --> 00:01:47,846
he stole one of your friends' idea
for his graduation project

9
00:01:47,847 --> 00:01:51,377
when he did his postgraduate study?

10
00:01:51,886 --> 00:01:53,177
He already told me about it.

11
00:01:53,647 --> 00:01:54,926
Due to that,

12
00:01:54,927 --> 00:01:56,856
he lost many of his best friends.

13
00:01:56,886 --> 00:01:58,257
He regretted it.

14
00:02:02,687 --> 00:02:03,696
However,

15
00:02:03,847 --> 00:02:05,365
there's a positive side to everything.

16
00:02:05,366 --> 00:02:06,846
You wouldn't have gotten married
to my brother

17
00:02:06,847 --> 00:02:08,496
had he not done so.

18
00:02:08,567 --> 00:02:10,165
If so, it's impossible for us

19
00:02:10,166 --> 00:02:11,897
to be together now.

20
00:02:13,046 --> 00:02:16,896
Life is truly magical.

21
00:02:17,606 --> 00:02:18,286
Why did you call me here

22
00:02:18,287 --> 00:02:19,817
to view the house all of a sudden?

23
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:21,416
Just have a look at it.

24
00:02:21,886 --> 00:02:22,777
What do you think?

25
00:02:29,446 --> 00:02:30,736
It's pretty good.

26
00:02:30,766 --> 00:02:32,136
What? Do you intend to buy it?

27
00:02:32,166 --> 00:02:33,136
Not at all.

28
00:02:34,007 --> 00:02:36,617
I don't have the money.

29
00:02:38,967 --> 00:02:40,366
One of my friends

30
00:02:40,367 --> 00:02:42,686
went abroad all of a sudden.

31
00:02:42,687 --> 00:02:44,537
He told me to look after
his house for him.

32
00:02:44,606 --> 00:02:46,896
I don't have time for that.

33
00:02:47,206 --> 00:02:48,006
Am I right?

34
00:02:48,007 --> 00:02:49,016
When I think about it,

35
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:50,366
you're the best candidate for the task.

36
00:02:50,367 --> 00:02:52,257
This way, you don't need
to travel back and forth.

37
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:54,777
Are you sure about that?

38
00:02:54,886 --> 00:02:56,217
Don't I need to pay the rent?

39
00:02:57,127 --> 00:02:58,286
I'm looking after the house for him.

40
00:02:58,287 --> 00:03:00,097
He has to pay me instead.

41
00:03:04,326 --> 00:03:05,445
What a coincidence.

42
00:03:05,446 --> 00:03:06,736
This place is quite near to my office.

43
00:03:07,046 --> 00:03:08,126
That's why when

44
00:03:08,127 --> 00:03:09,377
he told me about the location,

45
00:03:09,527 --> 00:03:12,406
I thought that you were
the best candidate for the task.

46
00:03:12,407 --> 00:03:14,537
It's just that you need
to take care of the house.

47
00:03:16,886 --> 00:03:17,896
Okay?

48
00:03:18,127 --> 00:03:19,617
I'll tell him about it
if you're okay with it.

49
00:03:19,847 --> 00:03:21,377
Sure.

50
00:03:21,766 --> 00:03:22,856
This is nice.

51
00:03:23,486 --> 00:03:24,217
Alright.

52
00:03:25,687 --> 00:03:26,736
(Are you serious?)

53
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:33,016
She said yes.

54
00:03:37,687 --> 00:03:38,537
It's so nice.

55
00:03:48,446 --> 00:03:49,856
Little tag-along?

56
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:51,377
Lan?

57
00:03:52,007 --> 00:03:53,257
I'm here.

58
00:03:53,486 --> 00:03:54,296
Look at you.

59
00:03:54,847 --> 00:03:55,566
How did it go?

60
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:56,456
I was right, wasn't I?

61
00:03:56,606 --> 00:03:58,696
We can always depend on Xiang Qian.

62
00:03:58,926 --> 00:04:00,456
She's the most resourceful child
we have.

63
00:04:00,926 --> 00:04:02,445
Xiang Zhong agreed to live there

64
00:04:02,446 --> 00:04:03,205
after viewing it.

65
00:04:03,206 --> 00:04:04,057
It's done, huh?

66
00:04:05,007 --> 00:04:05,806
This is great.

67
00:04:05,807 --> 00:04:06,686
She has both a job

68
00:04:06,687 --> 00:04:07,885
and a place to live in.

69
00:04:07,886 --> 00:04:09,377
We can rest at ease now.

70
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:11,016
Look. Isn't it great?

71
00:04:11,527 --> 00:04:12,497
Let's "like" the post.

72
00:04:13,127 --> 00:04:14,257
Come on.

73
00:04:14,446 --> 00:04:16,176
Niu, press it for us.

74
00:04:18,127 --> 00:04:19,205
He pressed it.

75
00:04:19,206 --> 00:04:19,806
You're something else.

76
00:04:19,807 --> 00:04:20,485
Don't do that.

77
00:04:20,486 --> 00:04:21,696
- Be gentle.
- Where's your father?

78
00:04:21,846 --> 00:04:23,057
Why is he ignoring you?

79
00:04:23,766 --> 00:04:24,845
Did he go drinking again?

80
00:04:24,846 --> 00:04:26,536
He's afraid of you. Stop teasing him.

81
00:04:26,886 --> 00:04:28,776
Let's go and play.

82
00:04:37,167 --> 00:04:38,246
Zhong.

83
00:04:38,247 --> 00:04:39,456
What are you doing here again?

84
00:04:39,526 --> 00:04:40,645
My class ended early.

85
00:04:40,646 --> 00:04:41,536
I came here to wait for you.

86
00:04:41,886 --> 00:04:42,776
Why are you waiting for me?

87
00:04:42,846 --> 00:04:43,445
You parked

88
00:04:43,446 --> 00:04:44,046
your electric scooter over there, right?

89
00:04:44,047 --> 00:04:45,006
Hand me the keys.

90
00:04:45,007 --> 00:04:46,057
I'll drive it back for you.

91
00:04:46,446 --> 00:04:46,885
No need for that.

92
00:04:46,886 --> 00:04:48,177
I'll drive it back on the weekend.

93
00:04:49,127 --> 00:04:51,096
My car is over there.

94
00:04:52,646 --> 00:04:53,576
I...

95
00:04:54,047 --> 00:04:54,926
Why don't we practice driving

96
00:04:54,927 --> 00:04:56,136
and help you to get familiar with it?

97
00:04:57,206 --> 00:04:58,136
No need for that.

98
00:05:18,766 --> 00:05:19,806
I think you can

99
00:05:19,807 --> 00:05:22,016
step on the gas accordingly.

100
00:05:22,127 --> 00:05:24,257
Just shut up. Don't talk.

101
00:05:25,206 --> 00:05:26,405
I can shut up.

102
00:05:26,406 --> 00:05:27,525
If you're in no hurry,

103
00:05:27,526 --> 00:05:28,497
I think...

104
00:05:33,406 --> 00:05:35,057
I can shut up.

105
00:05:35,206 --> 00:05:37,377
But you see, if you're in no hurry,

106
00:05:37,646 --> 00:05:38,926
if you maintain this speed,

107
00:05:38,927 --> 00:05:40,857
we can definitely reach home

108
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,456
by tomorrow night.

109
00:05:52,846 --> 00:05:55,016
Red light, stop!

110
00:05:58,167 --> 00:05:59,885
Can you stop following me?

111
00:05:59,886 --> 00:06:01,656
You're making me nervous.

112
00:06:17,286 --> 00:06:18,257
Green light, go.

113
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:39,817
Step on the brakes.

114
00:06:41,646 --> 00:06:42,896
Step on the brakes! My goodness!

115
00:06:43,086 --> 00:06:43,896
Xiang Zhong!

116
00:06:44,846 --> 00:06:45,445
Xiang Zhong!

117
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:46,126
Xiang Zhong!

118
00:06:46,127 --> 00:06:46,885
Are you okay?

119
00:06:46,886 --> 00:06:48,257
Let me see.

120
00:06:50,286 --> 00:06:51,126
The handbrake.

121
00:06:51,127 --> 00:06:52,405
Pull the handbrake.

122
00:06:52,406 --> 00:06:53,046
Where's the handbrake?

123
00:06:53,047 --> 00:06:53,937
Over there.

124
00:06:59,526 --> 00:07:01,006
Open the door.

125
00:07:01,007 --> 00:07:01,696
Don't be nervous.

126
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:03,377
Come. Slowly.

127
00:07:03,687 --> 00:07:04,617
Come.

128
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:05,937
Come.

129
00:07:06,247 --> 00:07:07,257
You're okay, right?

130
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:08,536
Good.

131
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:09,177
Good.

132
00:07:09,646 --> 00:07:10,576
At least you're fine.

133
00:07:11,727 --> 00:07:12,497
Be careful.

134
00:07:12,607 --> 00:07:13,536
There's no rush.

135
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:14,366
Slowly.

136
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:15,765
- This won't do.
- What?

137
00:07:15,766 --> 00:07:17,177
This won't do.

138
00:07:20,367 --> 00:07:22,977
That was terrifying!

139
00:07:23,646 --> 00:07:25,297
This is normal.

140
00:07:25,807 --> 00:07:28,486
Is driving that terrifying?

141
00:07:28,487 --> 00:07:29,806
It's all your fault.

142
00:07:29,807 --> 00:07:31,336
You made me drive.

143
00:07:31,381 --> 00:07:33,486
It's been so long since I last drove.

144
00:07:33,487 --> 00:07:35,617
That was terrifying.

145
00:07:36,007 --> 00:07:37,417
Let's stop, then.

146
00:07:39,727 --> 00:07:41,896
That was so terrifying.

147
00:07:44,526 --> 00:07:45,246
Get in.

148
00:07:45,247 --> 00:07:46,216
I'll drive.

149
00:08:13,646 --> 00:08:14,806
(A buddy of mine, who fell out of love,)

150
00:08:14,807 --> 00:08:15,845
(requested this song)

151
00:08:15,846 --> 00:08:17,726
(for his ex-lover.)

152
00:08:17,727 --> 00:08:18,686
(He wishes)

153
00:08:18,687 --> 00:08:20,377
(that he and his ex-lover)

154
00:08:20,646 --> 00:08:21,686
(can forgive each other)

155
00:08:21,687 --> 00:08:24,456
(even if they do drift apart
on this long road called life.)

156
00:08:24,886 --> 00:08:26,845
(Here's "Look Into My Eyes and Tell Me")

157
00:08:26,846 --> 00:08:27,566
(for all of our listeners.)

158
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:30,937
♪Can you look at me in the eyes?♪

159
00:08:31,927 --> 00:08:36,297
♪When will you tell me?♪

160
00:08:36,567 --> 00:08:39,337
♪Look into my eyes and tell me♪

161
00:08:40,207 --> 00:08:44,296
♪Maybe I'm overthinking it♪

162
00:08:44,686 --> 00:08:47,816
♪You said nothing♪

163
00:08:48,646 --> 00:08:52,656
♪I acted nonchalantly♪

164
00:08:53,046 --> 00:08:55,936
♪Forget it. Keep it to yourself♪

165
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:02,016
Why did you turn it off?

166
00:09:02,367 --> 00:09:03,977
Did you request that song?

167
00:09:04,487 --> 00:09:05,966
How could that be?

168
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:07,977
If not, why did you turn
on the radio for no reason?

169
00:09:11,046 --> 00:09:12,617
Just now,

170
00:09:13,007 --> 00:09:14,737
it was kind of awkward.

171
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,416
You know that it was awkward too, huh?

172
00:09:19,406 --> 00:09:20,857
What do you mean by that?

173
00:09:21,447 --> 00:09:22,765
I'll stop the car.

174
00:09:22,766 --> 00:09:23,726
I'll get off.

175
00:09:23,727 --> 00:09:25,176
You can drive yourself back, okay?

176
00:09:25,967 --> 00:09:27,525
What did you mean by that?

177
00:09:27,526 --> 00:09:28,565
Look at me.

178
00:09:28,566 --> 00:09:30,217
It was awkward trying to chat...

179
00:09:35,247 --> 00:09:36,337
Sorry.

180
00:09:36,926 --> 00:09:38,097
I'm truly sorry.

181
00:09:42,847 --> 00:09:43,977
I...

182
00:09:44,886 --> 00:09:47,206
I was getting agitated.

183
00:09:47,207 --> 00:09:48,697
That's why I started spouting nonsense.

184
00:09:49,847 --> 00:09:51,337
Sorry.

185
00:09:51,766 --> 00:09:52,726
I shouldn't have done so.

186
00:09:52,727 --> 00:09:53,846
I'll take back my words.

187
00:09:53,847 --> 00:09:56,337
I'll take all of my words back.

188
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:58,337
I'll take back the song request too.

189
00:10:00,007 --> 00:10:00,936
Sorry about that.

190
00:10:12,207 --> 00:10:13,776
You look so pretty when you smile.

191
00:10:20,327 --> 00:10:21,737
You look even prettier when you don't.

192
00:10:24,566 --> 00:10:26,497
Deng Haiyang, let me warn you.

193
00:10:26,566 --> 00:10:27,486
I may be sitting in your car,

194
00:10:27,487 --> 00:10:29,056
but that doesn't mean
I have certain intentions.

195
00:10:33,327 --> 00:10:34,416
Agreed.

196
00:10:36,646 --> 00:10:38,016
I don't have any intentions either.

197
00:10:39,327 --> 00:10:40,565
Both of us don't have any intentions.

198
00:10:40,566 --> 00:10:43,497
We have no intentions toward each other.

199
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:06,896
Xiang Nan,

200
00:11:07,286 --> 00:11:09,776
what has Jiaqiao been busy
with all this while?

201
00:11:09,926 --> 00:11:11,217
Why is she never home?

202
00:11:11,406 --> 00:11:12,656
I don't know.

203
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,896
Did she get into another relationship?

204
00:11:21,286 --> 00:11:22,217
What's the matter?

205
00:11:23,207 --> 00:11:24,377
I don't know either.

206
00:11:27,886 --> 00:11:28,405
Are you guys

207
00:11:28,406 --> 00:11:29,816
hiding something from me?

208
00:11:30,046 --> 00:11:31,737
That's not it. What's wrong?

209
00:11:32,286 --> 00:11:33,097
It's nothing.

210
00:11:35,406 --> 00:11:36,126
Rest early.

211
00:11:36,127 --> 00:11:37,217
I'll go to sleep first.

212
00:11:37,327 --> 00:11:38,257
Go ahead.

213
00:12:02,607 --> 00:12:03,617
Zhong, what's wrong?

214
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:09,902
(Tenancy Agreement Party B: Xiang Zhijun)
What are you doing?

215
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,697
Why did you guys
join hands to deceive me?

216
00:12:12,286 --> 00:12:13,206
The house we viewed last time,

217
00:12:13,207 --> 00:12:14,936
Dad and Mom rented it for me.

218
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,416
Why didn't you tell me the truth?

219
00:12:18,007 --> 00:12:19,217
Just stay there, won't you?

220
00:12:19,806 --> 00:12:21,285
They gave me a mission.

221
00:12:21,286 --> 00:12:22,857
It was to convince you
to stay in the unit.

222
00:12:23,007 --> 00:12:24,377
They didn't want me
to tell you the truth.

223
00:12:24,487 --> 00:12:26,136
Are you willing to stay there
if you were in my shoes?

224
00:12:26,686 --> 00:12:28,126
They're no longer young.

225
00:12:28,127 --> 00:12:29,697
It isn't easy for them to save money.

226
00:12:29,727 --> 00:12:31,617
And now, they're renting
a house for me in Shanghai?

227
00:12:31,646 --> 00:12:33,217
Aren't I sponging them off?

228
00:12:34,566 --> 00:12:36,136
Just take it as me
renting the house, okay?

229
00:12:36,447 --> 00:12:37,925
How are you renting it?

230
00:12:37,926 --> 00:12:39,486
You still have a family to raise.

231
00:12:39,487 --> 00:12:41,257
It's not like your fortune
was a windfall.

232
00:12:42,127 --> 00:12:43,805
If you don't stay there,

233
00:12:43,806 --> 00:12:45,697
Dad and Mom will be upset again.

234
00:12:46,727 --> 00:12:48,377
They're upset about plenty of things.

235
00:12:48,686 --> 00:12:50,536
Anyway, I won't be staying there.

236
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:52,885
In the future, just tell them

237
00:12:52,886 --> 00:12:53,966
to find me directly.

238
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:55,296
Can you please stay out of my affairs?

239
00:12:55,487 --> 00:12:56,246
Why didn't you

240
00:12:56,247 --> 00:12:57,285
go and tell them about it?

241
00:12:57,286 --> 00:12:58,377
Why did you come and find me instead?

242
00:12:59,046 --> 00:13:00,737
I'm a busybody.

243
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:02,337
I'm wrong no matter what I do.

244
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:03,006
Listen up.

245
00:13:03,007 --> 00:13:04,416
We've already paid the deposit.

246
00:13:04,487 --> 00:13:05,685
If you cancel the rent now,

247
00:13:05,686 --> 00:13:06,966
you'll be breaching the contract.

248
00:13:06,967 --> 00:13:07,805
We won't get a single cent back.

249
00:13:07,806 --> 00:13:08,816
You should think twice.

250
00:13:16,967 --> 00:13:18,896
Miss, isn't the house great?

251
00:13:19,046 --> 00:13:20,337
The rent is cheap too.

252
00:13:20,487 --> 00:13:21,896
Everyone wants to rent it.

253
00:13:22,007 --> 00:13:23,885
Yeah, I know that it's a great house.

254
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:24,925
If it's that popular,

255
00:13:24,926 --> 00:13:26,377
just rent it out for me, okay?

256
00:13:27,207 --> 00:13:28,525
There's no issue with that.

257
00:13:28,526 --> 00:13:30,016
I can do that with a snap of my fingers.

258
00:13:30,087 --> 00:13:30,885
However, we've already

259
00:13:30,886 --> 00:13:32,086
signed a contract.

260
00:13:32,087 --> 00:13:33,285
If you're renting it out,

261
00:13:33,286 --> 00:13:34,816
it'll be considered
a breach of contract.

262
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:38,326
It's fine no matter what you do.

263
00:13:38,327 --> 00:13:39,896
Anyway, I'll stop renting the place.

264
00:13:40,727 --> 00:13:42,565
If you wish to stop renting the place,

265
00:13:42,566 --> 00:13:44,246
we won't be able to refund you

266
00:13:44,247 --> 00:13:45,416
the rent and the deposit.

267
00:13:45,526 --> 00:13:46,685
I said, I'll stop renting the place.

268
00:13:46,686 --> 00:13:48,217
Why can't I get a refund then?

269
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:50,165
Even so, we don't have a choice.

270
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:51,285
No one forced you guys

271
00:13:51,286 --> 00:13:53,097
to sign the contract back then?

272
00:13:56,686 --> 00:13:57,457
Miss,

273
00:13:57,727 --> 00:13:59,206
this is a great house.

274
00:13:59,207 --> 00:14:00,656
Why aren't you renting it?

275
00:14:00,847 --> 00:14:02,136
I can't afford it.

276
00:14:06,406 --> 00:14:07,097
Xiang Zhong.

277
00:14:07,327 --> 00:14:08,296
Xiang Zhong.

278
00:14:09,526 --> 00:14:11,016
What are you doing here?

279
00:14:11,127 --> 00:14:12,656
I was planning to look for you.

280
00:14:13,286 --> 00:14:14,296
What's wrong?

281
00:14:14,607 --> 00:14:15,925
You crashed the car yesterday.

